description: Encounter type for HIV exposed infant visit

description: An encounter type representing discovery of findings/symptoms during an initial primary care visit.

description: In-Patient Discharge (going out of hospitalization) encounter

description: In-Patient Registration (when the patient enters the InCare) encounter

description: CBS Recency Viral Load Lab Result encounter type

description: Confidential HIV Case Reporting for HIV Case-Based Surveillance

description: Non clinical encounter are encounters that don't involve  clinician meeting with the patient

name: Neo admission infant bellow 1 month encounter
description: Neo admission infant bellow 1 month encounter

name: Neo daily evaluation and orders encounter
description: Neo daily evaluation and orders encounter

name: IPD auto Observation or general followup encounter
description: IPD auto Observation or general followup encounter

name: Drug Order Encounter
description: Encounter type used for recording drug orders in an encounter when no existing encounter is available

name: Check In
description: Indicates the patient has done the required paperwork and check-in to begin a visit to the clinic/hospital.

name: Visit Note
description: Encounter where a full or abbreviated examination is done, usually leading to a presumptive or confirmed diagnosis, recorded by the examining clinician.

name: Check Out
description: The patient is explicitly leaving the hospital/clinic. (Usually no formal encounter is captured for this.)

name: Attachment Upload
description: Encounters used to record uploads of attachments.

name: Inpatient Note
description: A short free-text note written by a clinician about an inpatient during their stay

name: Transfer Request
description: A stand-alone encounter type for a transfer request not part of a larger note

name: Bed Assignment
description: Assigning a new bed to a patient without admitting or transferring them

name: Cancel ADT
description: An encounter that notes that a request to admit/transfer/discharge a patient is being overridden
